<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Offers Choice of 5 Sites for Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202184694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1700 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 2 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin had a meeting with State Duma Speaker Ivan 
Rybkin on Wednesday to discuss the place of a new residence for 
the lower chamber of the Russian parliament. 
  The Duma is now situated in the former Comecon building and 
lawmakers complain that it is incovenient for work. 
  The government offered parliamentarians five new places, 
including the building of the Russian Management Academy in the 
south west of the capital and two buildings in downtown Moscow. 
  No reports whether the prime minister and the Duma speaker 
had reached any agreement were available. 
  However, several lawmakers said that the Duma continues to 
insist that the former parliament building which was pounded by 
tanks during the October revolt and then transferred to the 
government, be returned to the legislature. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

