<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Departs for Georgia To Meet Shevardnadze </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302052894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0505 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302052894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Excerpt] Moscow, 3 February -- President of the Russian 
Federation Boris Yeltsin has left Moscow on an official visit to 
Georgia early this morning. The program of his one-day visit is 
going to be very busy. 
  Immediately after his arrival in the Georgian capital and 
the 
greeting ceremony at the airport Yeltsin will have one-to-one 
talks with Eduard Shevardnadze. After that, the 
Russian-Georgian talks will continue with an extended number of 
participants. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

