<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments Before Leaving </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302061794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0530 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302061794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 3 February--Boris Yeltsin has stated that he 
will sign the friendship, good-neighborliness and cooperation 
Treaty in Tbilisi today but its ratification in the parliament 
will be delayed until the conflicts in Abkhazia and South 
Ossetia are fully resolved. The President stated this at the 
Vnukovo-2 airport before his departure for an official visit to 
Georgia. The President admitted that situation in South Ossetia 
and Abkhazia "create problems which should be solved on the 
step-by-step basis." 
  Answering the ITAR-TASS correspondent's question on the main 
aims of his visit, the President said: "First of all, we are 
trying to stop bloodshed in Georgia. Russia cannot wait 
indifferently for things to sort themselves out over there." 
The second aim of the visit, said Yeltsin, is joint defense of 
the borders and the third is joint use and protection of the 
railways. The President also noted the need for a full-scale 
treaty with Georgia as well as a number of military-technical 
agreements. 

</TEXT>

