<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Comments Before Leaving for Tbilisi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302093794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0900 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Early this morning the presidential airplane took 
off for Tbilisi. The program for Yeltsin's one-day trip to the 
Georgian capital is very busy. 
  [Begin Yeltsin recording] We will sign the treaty today, 
after all, but we will wait with ratification until the conflict 
is completely settled, and this will suit both our Caucasian 
republics and, I think, Georgia and Russia as a whole. 
  Together with the CSCE and EEC, Russia is mediating in order 
to somehow halt the bloodshed there; second, to protect the 
border jointly; third, jointly to exploit railways and protect 
them against attacks, accordingly; fourth, a full-scale treaty 
to be signed with Georgia as well as military-technical 
agreements, an accord. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

