<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Russian Timetable for Estonian Troop Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202164694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1600 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia has not yet presented a timetable for troop 
withdrawal from Estonia even though one was expected at the 
present round of Estonian-Russian talks which took place near 
Moscow yesterday and today. Juri Kahn, Estonian ambassador to 
Moscow, who is the leader of the economic issues working group 
at the talks on the Estonian side, told Estonian Radio that 
Russia has promised to present a timetable for the troop 
withdrawal if Estonia accepts the agreement on Russian military 
pensioners as designed by Russia. 
  According to Juri Kahn, Estonia and Russia did not sign any 
documents during this round of talks. However, some were 
prepared, to be signed at the next round of talks. This is due 
at Lohusalu in Estonia on 1 and 2 March. 

</TEXT>

