<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks on Baykonur Continue in Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202125694 Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network in Russian 
0830 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A working meeting of experts from the Russian 
Federation and the Republic of Kazakhstan is continuing in 
Moscow. They are discussing the status of the Baykonur 
cosmodrome and the town of Leninsk and conditions for their use. 
At the moment the Kazakh side is still refusing to recognize 
Baykonur as a Russian military base and is insisting on its 
demilitarization, since Kazakhstan's constitution stipulates 
that there must not be any foreign military bases on the 
republic's territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

