<H3> <TI>   French Defense Minister Leotard, Delegation Arrive 2 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202215894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2115 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 3 TASS -- A French military 
delegation led by Defence Minister Francois Leotard arrived in 
Moscow on Wednesday. 
  This is the first official visit to Russia by Leotard since 
his appointment French defence minister in the spring of 1993. 
  On February 3, the French delegation will meet with First 
Deputy Defence Minister Andrey Kokoshin and Chief of the Russian 
General Staff Mikhail Kolesnikov. Leotard will visit the Moscow 
All Arms Military School. Upon his return from Tbilisi where he 
flew today for talks, Russian Defence Minister Pavel will take 
his French counterpart on a tour of an airborne division in Tula 
near Moscow. 
  The visit is part of the Russian-French bilateral agreement 
signed during Grachev's visit to France in January 1993 on 
mutual contacts, delegation exchanges and training Russian 
servicemen in France and their French colleagues in Russia. 
  Leotard also plans to meet with First Vice-Prime Minister 
Oleg Soskovets and Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev who visited 
France in the autumn of 1993. During the visit they signed 
bilateral agreements on cooperation to dismantle nuclear weapons 
in Russia and ensure their safe transportation. 

</TEXT>

