<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Media Barred From Government Meeting 3 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302083794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0739 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302083794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 3 TASS -- For the first time after 
the abortive Soviet coup in 1991 reporters were not allowed to a 
meeting of the Russian Government on Thursday [3 February]. 
  A spokesman of the government press service explained that, 
according to an order of the head of the government 
administration, only a correspondent of the government-run 
"ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA" newspaper will be allowed to attend the 
meetings [plural as received]. 
  Reporters of news agencies, television networks and other 
media are barred from now on. 
  The government is to discuss prospects for agriculture in 
1994, support to small-scale enterprises, state control over 
labour safety, the settlement of the Ossetian-Ingushi conflict, 
as well as the plan of government work for the first and second 
quarters of 1994. 

</TEXT>

