<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Continues Along Karabakh Frontline </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202151794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1443 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ARMENPRESS for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan February 2 TASS -- Sporadic fighting went on 
today along the Karabakh front-line. Azeri Army suffered 
considerable losses in its night offensive towards the town of 
Martuni, a source in the Karabakh military headquarters told 
ARMENPRESS. 
  On Tuesday night Azeri troops attacked the Armenian border 
settlement of Movses. After a three-hour shooting Armenian 
border troops pushed the enemy back to their previous positions, 
the press service of the Armenian Defence Ministry reported. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

