<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgian Premier's Letter to Aliyev Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202220194 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 27 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202220194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a letter to President Geydar Aliyev, Prime 
Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene said: 
  Mr. President, I have received your letter dated 28 November 
1993. Belgium is well aware of the destruction caused by the 
dispute in Daghlyk Karabakh and laments that state of affairs. 
In parallel with our president's tasks as the chairman of the 
European Union [EU] Committee, my country is making a diplomatic 
effort within the CSCE Minsk Group's framework to contribute 
toward the finding of a just solution to that dispute. Any 
decision for the solution of the problem must be in accordance 
with CSCE principles and provide for the maintenance of 
international borders and the protection of the rights of ethnic 
minorities. 
  Disturbed by the fate of hundreds of thousands of refugees, 
who are in serious condition, Belgium and its EU partners have 
recently decided to increase their humanitarian aid to that 
region. 
  Meanwhile, I am convinced that mutual cooperation between 
Belgium and Azerbaijan can be successfully improved. The 
Belgian Government is prepared to cooperate with you on that 
matter. 
  Mr. President, I wish to take this opportunity to convey my 
respects to you once again. 

</TEXT>

