<H3> <TI>   Talks on Baykonur End With No Result </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302194894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1810 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Veronika Romanenkova and Semen </F>
Ivanov] 
  [Excerpt] Moscow, 3 Feb (ITAR-TASS) -- Experts from Russia 
and Kazakhstan completed their consultations on the status and 
use of the Baykonur space launch site today with virtually no 
result. They merely adopted a protocol on the meeting, which 
stated a mutual wish of the two sides to hold another meeting in 
mid-February. 
  The Kazakh side did not submit any documents to be discussed 
during the consultations but focussed on criticizing the 
projects drawn up by the Russian delegation. According to some 
experts, this is the reason why the two sides failed to arrive 
at a compromise solution concerning Baykonur's future. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

