<H3> <TI>   Shokhin Says Money Merging Package With Belarus Not Ready </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302221094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1807 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Economics Minister Aleksandr Shokhin has 
said that the package of documents on the unification of the 
monetary systems of Russia and Belarus is not yet prepared, and 
that is why the unification agreement cannot be signed during 
Viktor Chernomyrdin's upcoming visit to Minsk. 
  The minister said he had learned of the premier's visit from 
the mass media and that he had never given his consent to 
signing the agreement. Shokhin recalled the fact that it was 
the prime minister who asked him to take up preparing the 
negotiations on the unification of the two countries' monetary 
systems. 
  Shokhin said the package of documents defining the procedure 
for the unification had not yet been prepared. He added that he 
had a meeting with one of Belarus' deputy prime ministers in 
Moscow last Friday. "We did not advertise this, but we detected 
a number of approaches to solving disputable issues. Now the 
task is to introduce the approaches into the text of an 
agreement," Shokhin was quoted as saying. With this aim in 
view, several Russian representatives left for Minsk for two to 
three days. "If the documents are to be, we must approve them at 
a government meeting," the minister pointed out. Only after 
this can the documents be signed, he added. 

</TEXT>

