<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kokoshin, France's Leotard Discuss Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302121994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1045 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostankin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 3 Feb -- This morning Andrey Kokoshin, first 
deputy defense minister of Russia, had a meeting with French 
Defense Minister Francois Leotard, who arrived in Moscow on an 
official visit on Wednesday. At the meeting Kokoshin said that 
"the Russian state leadership places great importance on the 
development of relations with France, including the military 
sphere. Our relations are being developed extremely carefully, 
incorporating both new realities and rich military traditions." 
  For his part, the French guest said that he was ready "to 
debate any security problems or crisis experienced by Russia." 
This is Francois Leotard's first official visit to Russia since 
his appointment to the post of the defense minister of France in 
spring 1993. 
  Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, chief of the general 
staff of the Russian Federation's Armed Forces, took part in the 
meeting, at which it was noted that close ties have recently 
formed between the two military departments. Army General Pavel 
Grachev, who visited France in January last year, signed an 
agreement on mutual contacts and, in particular, on exchanging 
military delegations, training Russian servicemen in France, and 
French servicemen in Russia. First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg 
Soskovets and Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, who visited Paris 
last autumn and whom Francois Leotard is planning to meet in 
Moscow, signed then the Russian- French agreement on cooperation 
in dismantling Russian nuclear weapons and ensuring reliability 
and safety during their transportation. 
  Francois Leotard will visit the Moscow army high command 
school today, meet Pavel Grachev on Friday, and visit the Tula 
airborne division. A Russian-French intergovernmental agreement 
on military cooperation is expected to be signed on Friday. 

</TEXT>

