<H3> <TI>   Grachev, Leotard in Car Accident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402100894 Paris AFP in English 0945 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0402100894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, Feb 4 (AFP) -- An armoured Zil limousine 
carrying Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev and his visiting 
French counterpart Francois Leotard crashed into a truck on a 
icy road in Moscow Friday [4 February] but nobody was hurt. 
  The car hit a truck in icy conditions as the two defence 
chiefs were heading to Olabino to visi the Tamaskaya guard, an 
AFP correspondent in the motorcade said. 
  The front of the armoured Zil car was badly crushed. The 
ministers later transferred to another vehicle. 

</TEXT>

