<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets Japanese Parliament Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302201894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1812 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vyacheslav Bantin] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo February 3 TASS -- Takako Doi, chairwoman of 
the lower chamber of the Japanese Parliament, met Gennadiy 
Burbulis, deputy of Russia's State Duma, on Thursday [2 
February]. The meeting is considered to be the first step 
toward establishing interparliamentary ties between the two 
countries. 
  Burbulis together with his American and Japanese 
counterparts 
participated in the trilateral forum on security in the north- 
Pacific region which closed here on Wednesday. 
  Burbulis emphasized the significance of his meeting with 
Takako Doi "from the point of view of a revival of the Russian 
Parliament's prestige and the authority of the Russian 
parliamentarians" in an interview with ITAR-TASS on Thursday. 
  According to him, Takako doi showed much interest in the 
process of forming the new Russian Parliament and emphasized 
that it was important to establish fruitful cooperation between 
the Russian and Japanese lawmakers as soon as possible. 
  She called on the Russian Parliament to resume the 
activities 
of the Russo-Japanese parliamentary committee which was 
suspended because of the dissolvement of the former Supreme 
Soviet. 
  Takako Doi expressed grave concern about the fact that the 
last transformations inside Russia's Government might result in 
curtailing the economic reforms. In response, Burbulis, who 
represents the "Russia's Choice" faction in the lower chamber of 
Russia's Parliament, said that the new Russian Constitution, 
which was adopted on December 12, 1993, had for the first time 
given the chance to secure political stability in the country. 
  "In no case shall we leave President Boris Yeltsin in 
isolation, without the indispensable support of the 
professionals who carried out the economic reforms," he 
emphasized. 
  In his opinion, joint work of President yeltsin and Premier 
Viktor chernomyrdin Is a sure guaranty of stability inside 
Russia. 
  "Boris Yeltsin has received enough powers to provide for a 
stable and competent system of government. As for Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, he has always demonstrated his ability to make 
strategic decisions which were in line with the course of 
economic reforms," he said. 
  "Today it should have been dangerous to let the union 
between 
the president and the chairman of goverment collapse," he 
emphasized. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

