<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Policy Planning Consultations Begin in Tokyo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302154594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1430 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Varlamov] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo February 3 TASS--Two-day Russo-Japanese 
consultations on foreign policy planning at foreign department 
official level began in Tokyo today. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS head of the Russian 
delegation, chief of the Russian Foreign Ministry Analysis and 
Prognosis Department Ednan Agayev said that the range of 
problems, which is being discussed at the meeting, embraces not 
only general tendencies of the foreign policy situation in the 
world, but also problems, concerning the development of 
Asia-Pacific region, in particular, the development of 
integration processes. According to him, the evolution of 
Russian and Japanese approaches towards ensuring regional 
security will also be an important topic for exchange of views. 
  Annual consultations on foreign policy planning between 
foreign ministries of the two country are being held since 1992 
and have become a form of regular contacts between the two 
foreign departments. Consultations are held alternately in 
Moscow and Tokyo. They are serving as mutual exchange of 
information about questions, concerning the formation and 
development of foreign policies of the countries and also about 
the international situation. 

</TEXT>

