<H3> <TI>   Vorontsov's Appointment as Ambassador to U.S. Not Confirmed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0302134094 Moscow KOMMERSANT-DAILY in Russian 3 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> MK0302134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMMERSANT-DAILY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [International Department report: "Reshuffles at Russian </F>
Foreign Ministry. Russian Ambassador to U.S. Has Not Yet Been 
Appointed"] 
  [Text] SEGODNYA, citing "diplomatic sources," has reported 
that Yuliy Vorontsov, currently Russia's permanent 
representative at the United Nations, has been appointed 
Russia's new ambassador to Washington. Correspondingly, he has 
been replaced at the United Nations by Deputy Foreign Minister 
Sergey Lavrov. However, Deputy Foreign Minister Sergey Krylov, 
who is in charge of personnel policy, did not confirm this 
report yesterday to KOMMERSANT-DAILY's correspondent. Both 
Vorontsov and Lavrov, according to unofficial information 
received by KOMMERSANT-DAILY, may in fact be appointed to the 
aforementioned posts. Currently Sergey Lavrov is at UN 
headquarters in New York. KOMMERSANT-DAILY plans to publish an 
interview with him in the near future. KOMMERSANT-DAILY will 
follow up on the subject once corresponding presidential edicts 
are signed. 

</TEXT>

