<H3> <TI>   Working Group Considers Long-Term Weapons Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0302140594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 3 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0302140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Own Information" report under the "News" rubric: "Session </F>
of Council on Military-Technical Policy"] 
  [Text] Moscow -- A session of the working group of the 
Council on Military-Technical Policy under the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Defense has been held at the Ministry of 
Defense under the chairmanship of First Deputy Minister Andrey 
Kokoshin. Major defense industry scientists, experts, and 
representatives of military science took part in the session. 
  In accordance with the Security Council decision "On 
Programs 
To Develop and Manufacture Promising Types of Weapons and 
Military Hardware" dated 19 January 1994, an amplified draft of 
a long-term weapons program was examined. 

