<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Passes Law on Forming Regional Bodies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302221894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1807 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Thursday the Ukrainian Supreme Council passed a 
law on the formation of local power and self-government bodies. 
According to the law, after the elections, which will be held on 
June 26 simultaneously with presidential elections, the 
Ukrainian law on presidential representatives will become 
ineffective. 
  Under the law, chairmen of local councils of people's 
deputies are elected by the population of a region and become 
heads of executive committees of the corresponding councils. 
They are subordinate to the corresponding local councils. 
  In issues related to authorities of the state and executive 
powers, local councils are subordinate to the Cabinet and 
executive bodies of superior councils. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

