<H3> <TI>   IMF Experts Encourage Close Ties With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0402090594 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0402090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Experts of the IMF, who recently visited Belarus, 
have encouraged the Belarusian leadership's efforts to develop 
close economic ties with Russia. They underlined the advantages 
of economic integration with Russia. At the same time, these 
advantages, according to expert opinions, do not imply the 
creation of a monetary and credit union. According to them, one 
should take into account the negative economic results for 
Belarus of the unification of the monetary and credit systems if 
Russia fails to secure its economic stabilization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-36302 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov024_s_94001" </HT>


