<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev, Patsatsia on Signing Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302232394 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1607 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302232394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Prime Minister Otar Patsatsia and Russian </F>
Defense Minister Pavel Grachev by unidentified correspondent in 
Tbilisi on 3 February--recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Otar Patsatsia] This is an historic occasion. 
It not only has political importance but also economic 
importance. We are witnessing deep forms of fraternity and 
friendship between the Georgian and Russian peoples, and these 
are at the stage of restoration. It is necessary for us to 
restore them. We pin great hopes on this large package [of 
agreements] that was just signed. This will provide an impetus 
in the development of the economy in our republic. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you. 
  [Pavel Grachev] These issues were agreed upon at the level 
of working groups. A consent has been acquired from the two 
presidents. I had a talk with Eduard Ambrosyevich Shevardnadze 
on this subject yesterday. He confirmed all these intentions, 
and this morning our experts finished the text of the protocol 
we signed. 
  [Correspondent] Will the issue of the return of refugees to 
Abkhazia be discussed, and how safe would it be? 
  [Grachev] All issues linked with the further work, even the 
the principal treaty our presidents will sign, will certainly be 
linked with the situation in Abkhazia as well as the situation 
in South Ossetia. Indeed, without a stable political situation 
in the Georgian state, all of these good undertakings, good 
protocols, and all other good things will not gain momentum. A 
firm, good, and stable political situation is required. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

