<F P=103> LD0302203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press center of the Georgian Defense Ministry 
told Interfax that another explosion took place today at about 
13:00 in the apartment of Georgian Deputy Defense Minister Niki 
Kekelidze, killed by the first one last night. The second 
explosion was much less powerful, but caused a slight concussion 
to Georgian Defense Minister Georgiy Karkarashvili, who came to 
see the site of the incident. 
  The press center said that no one except the minister was 
hurt and suggested that a booby trap had been installed in 
Kekelidze's apartment. 
  Meanwhile, the press center of the Georgian Interior 
Ministry 
failed to confirm the information on the second explosion. 

