<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sentence Against Ilascu Group Annulled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302195494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0302195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today in Chisinau the Penal Judiciary Collegium of 
the Supreme Court of the Republic of Moldova examined the case 
and annulled the sentence passed on 9 December 1993 against the 
[Ilie] Ilascu group. The case is to be returned to the State 
Prosecutor's Office of the Republic of Moldova in view of 
opening penal procedures against the judges belonging to the 
anti-constitutional court in Tiraspol, who participated in the 
passing of the illegitimate sentence that jeopardized the life, 
freedom, and health of those sentenced. 
  At the same time the Moldovan body decided to terminate the 
preventive arrest of the six [members of the Ilascu group]. 
  In a statement made to our correspondent, Nicolae Gore, a 
member of the Supreme Court of Justice of the Republic of 
Moldova, emphasized the fact that today's court ruling annuls 
the Tiraspol sentence and all its consequences. According to 
the laws of the Republic of Moldova, as soon as the sentence was 
annulled, the Ilascu group has to be released from jail, added 
Nicolae Gore. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

