<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma To Consider Yeltsin Warning on Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402095094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0931 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 4 TASS--The Russian State Duma will 
discuss the address of the Russian president, in which he warned 
lawmakers against violating the Constitution, while adopting the 
permanent procedural rules, speaker Ivan Rybkin told the lower 
chamber on Friday. The discussion is scheduled for next week. 
  Boris Yeltsin sent an address to both chambers of the 
Russian 
parliament reminding them that, according to the Constitution, 
decisions are considered adopted if they receive support of more 
than a half of the total constitutionally-envisaged number of 
deputies. 
  However, while adopting interim procedural rules, lawmakers 
interpreted the notion of the "total number of deputies" as the 
total number of elected lawmakers, although several seats are 
still vacant in each of the chambers. 
  The president requested the deputies "to bring the interim 
rules in accordance with the Constitution". 

</TEXT>

