<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Creates National Security Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402105294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0947 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Mainayev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek February 4 TASS -- The president of 
Kyrgyzstan decreed on Friday to create the National Security 
Council which is to become a consultative body at the president 
[as received] and will draft security decisions for the head of 
state. 
  The council is to consider strategic problems of state, 
economic, ecological and other types of security. 
  It is also to expose internal and external threats to 
Kyrgyzstan, assist the drafting of major guidelines of the 
national security strategy, prepare recommendations for the 
president on urgent decisions to avert extraordinary situations 
and other problems. 
  The council united the defence, interior, security 
ministers, 
the commander of the National Guard, several government members. 

</TEXT>

