<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier: Relations With Russia Unsatisfactory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302231494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1939 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302231494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lithuanian Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius told 
INTERFAX on Thursday that he is not satisfied with the latest 
relations with Russia. 
  In particular, the premier said, immediately after signing 
the treaty on most favored trading status with Russia a few 
months ago the Lithuanian side sent a note to Moscow. However, 
the Russian side has not yet responded, so the treaty cannot 
come into force. 
  Referring to unofficial reports, the premier said that the 
Russian side is trying to link these issues with other problems, 
in particular with "some aspects of relations between Lithuania 
and the Kaliningrad region of Russia." 

</TEXT>

