<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Urges Turkish Role in Karabakh Peace Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0302182994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0302182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Ali Dogan in Baku] </F>
  [Text] Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev has talked to 
Turkish reporters in Baku before his visit to Turkey. He said 
that Azerbaijan want peace but that the first and foremost 
condition is that Armenia withdraw from the Azerbaijani 
territory it has occupied. Pointing out that the Russian 
proposal for an immediate cease-fire was rejected because this 
condition had not been met, Aliyev stressed that Azerbaijan 
definitely wants Turkey to participate in the peacekeeping force 
Russia intends to station in Karabakh. Recalling that he will 
be making an official visit to Turkey as the guest of President 
Suleyman Demirel between 8 and 11 February, Aliyev added that 
this visit will constitute a stepping stone to further develop 
the existing bilateral relations. He noted that he will be 
conducting talks on all issues with Turkey and that the 
Ceyhan-Baku oil pipeline issue will also be taken up. 

