<H3> <TI>   Navy Denies Kronshtadt Base To Be Relocated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0302152194 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 3 Feb 94 First 
Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM0302152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Sergey Krayukhin report: "Kronshtadt Remains Russian Naval </F>
Base"] 
  [Excerpts] A report on an "Ostankino" television and radio 
company program and in other organs of the mass media stated 
that during B.N. Yeltsin's visit to St. Petersburg the Russian 
Federation president and the city Mayor A. Sobchak discussed the 
future prospects for turning Kronshtadt into a free economic 
zone and in this connection the naval base's relocation. 
[passage omitted] 
  Editorial note: On the basis of information from sources 
within the Russian Navy Main Staff, IZVESTIYA has been informed 
that as yet no specific decision has been made concerning 
Kronshtadt. Relocating this naval base really does require 
enormous resources which nobody has appropriated, and nobody has 
produced a plan to set up a base in another location. Such an 
order has not been given. Kronshtadt will remain a Russian 
naval base for a long time to come. 

</TEXT>

