94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0302161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Non-Stop" rubric: </F>
"Yeltsin's Visit to Tbilisi May End in Georgia's Occupation"] 
  [Text] Volunteers of the Caucasus People's Confederation 
[CPC] will immediately come to the rescue of Abkhazia and South 
Ossetia if the upcoming Russian-Georgian agreement exacerbates 
the situation there, Ali Aliyev, chairman of the CPC parliament, 
told your MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS correspondent. According to 
Aliyev, last year formations of the Abkhaz and "confederate" 
forces were mightily armed thanks to captured Georgian armored 
vehicles and heavy artillery. Last year, Captain 1st Rank 
Aliyev said, we had the military and moral potential enough to 
advance through half of Georgia and to reach Kutaisi. 
  The South Ossetian parliament asked the Russian Federation 
Council not to ratify the agreement until the Georgian-South 
Ossetian conflict is resolved. 

