<H3> <TI>   Economic, Political Issues Discussed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402184594 Kiev UKRINFORM in Russian 1639 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UKRINFORM </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Viktor Demidenko] </F>
  [Text] Kiev, 4 Feb -- Economic and political problems 
facing the Crimean Republic as a constituent part of Ukraine 
were discussed by Ukraine's President Leonid Kravchuk and 
Crimean Republic President Yuriy Meshkov at their working 
meeting held here today. The main attention was paid to economic 
issues, in particular, to the pattern of developing economic 
relations between Crimea and its traditional partners in the 
Russian Federation and other CIS countries, offered by Yuriy 
Meshkov. 
  An agreement was reached during the meeting on setting up a 
working group of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine and the 
government of the autonomous republic that will consider 
specific proposals and calculations of the economic development 
of Crimea. Also discussed was the mechanism of working relations 
between the president of Ukraine and the president of the 
Crimean Republic. 
  The meeting was held in an atmosphere of openness and 
constructive mutual understanding. 

</TEXT>

