<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Approves Resolution on Structure, Personnel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402134294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1202 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 4 TASS -- On Friday, the Russian 
State Duma adopted a resolution, sponsored by Duma chairman Ivan 
Rybkin, determining the chamber's structure and staff. 
  The Duma's activity will be supported by 677 full-time 
staffers, not including technicians. In addition, faction and 
deputy group apparatuses are to be manned by 132 people, along 
with the 386 support personnel approved for the Duma's 
committees and commissions. 
  The Duma's apparatus is to have the status of a legal 
entity. 
It was suggested that the Duma chairman continue working on the 
formation of the apparatus in accordance with the chamber's 
structure. 
  It was resolved that workers in the parliament's lower 
chamber will be considered equal to comparable workers in the 
apparatus of the Russian Federation Government in terms of 
salary, and social, material, and medical support. Finally, the 
Duma resolved that its leadership shall request the government 
to take the appropriate steps towards implementing this 
resolution. 

</TEXT>

