<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kebich Favors Economic Alliance With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502131994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1219 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0502131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 5 TASS -- Belarusian Prime Minister 
Vyacheslav Kebich regards as his main political objective the 
restoration of an economic alliance with Russia. In his 
interview with SELSKAYA ZHIZN he refuted allegations that the 
joining of the rouble zone by Belarus is undermining its 
sovereignty, or that this decision means a kind of charity on 
the part of Russia. "In this case those European politicians who 
are working for the introduction of a common instrument of 
payment for europe are bad patriots either," Kebich stressed. 
  In his opinion, the root cause of Gaydar's resignation is 
much deeper than the problem of signing an agreement on the 
unification of monetary systems of Russia and Belarus. "In 
general terms, it could be described as the difference in views 
between the prime minister and the deputy prime minister over 
the way the reform should be developed," he said. 
  The rouble zone will not mean a political and economic 
alliance, it will be nothing but a common financial and monetary 
system. According to Kebich, "in conditions of a common monetary 
system, Belarus will have a chance to follow its own path. The 
same is true of Russia. We have complete understanding on that 
matter with Russian leaders." 

</TEXT>

