<H3> <TI>   Hryb: Domestic, Foreign Policy To Remain Unchanged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402205394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1910 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Aleksandr Lyushkevich for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk February 4 TASS -- The Belarusian foreign and 
domestic policy will remain unchanged, newly elected Belarusian 
Parliament Speaker Myechyslaw Hryb told foreign ambassadors to 
Belarus here today. The strategic goals are consolidation of 
independence and transformation of Belarus into a neutral state. 
  In his words, the republic attaches great importance to a 
recent visit of U.S. President Bill Clinton which laid down the 
basis of further bilateral cooperation in the political and 
economic spheres. 
  He also praised negotiations of Vyacheslav Kebich and 
Stanislav Shushkevich with Russian President Boris Yeltsin and 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. The speaker said further 
Russian-Belarusian integration with the future unification of 
their monetary systems is a vital necessity without which 
Belarus will collapse. 
  The formation of Russian-Belarusian economic union will take 
several months due to the need to sign 40 agreements. 

</TEXT>

