<H3> <TI>   Electoral Commission Rejects Idea of Poll </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402134694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0402134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Central Electoral Commission of the Republic of 
Moldova has rejected the proposal put forward by the president 
and by the presidium of the Moldovan Parliament to organize 
simultaneously with the parliamentary elections on 27 February a 
sociological poll in order to confirm the independence of the 
Republic of Moldova, Chisinau Television reports. 
  The Commission justified this decision by saying that it is 
not entitled to carry out such polls because the only duty of 
the commission is to organize parliamentary elections. 

</TEXT>

