  [Text] Almaty -- According to a report from the public 
relations department of the Kazakhstan National Security 
Committee, an agreement on cooperation and collaboration has 
been signed between the Kazakhstan National Security Committee 
and the Tajikistan State Committee for National Security. 
  The sides agreed on joint measures in the fight against 
contraband, corruption, organized crime, international 
terrorism, and the unlawful movement of narcotics, psychotropic 
substances, and weapons. Tajikistan's national security organs 
will be given assistance by their Kazakhstan colleagues in the 
training of cadres. 

