<H3> <TI>   Decree Demands Payment Up-Front for Goods </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0402172194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 3 Feb 94 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM0402172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS, and </F>
LOGOTIP-KP column under the general heading: "One-Liners"] 
  [Text] Kyrgyzstan -- The republic's government has adopted 
a decree which requires manufacturing enterprises to dispatch 
output, raw materials, or semimanufactures only after prepayment 
by their customers. At the same time maximum timeframes for 
processing payments -- from three to seven banking days -- have 
been set. A fine of double the rate of interest for every day's 
delay will henceforth be exacted for any holdup. 

</TEXT>

