<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   IMF Expresses Concern on Implementation of Reforms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602193594 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Russian 1700 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As reported in the press, an IMF delegation is 
visiting Kyrgyzstan. The delegation, led by Peter Voeller, is 
providing the republic with technical assistance for the 
implementation of socioeconomic reforms. 
  The delegation was received by Askar Akayev, the president 
of 
the Kyrgyz Republic. 
  IMF representatives expressed serious concern over the way 
reforms were being implemented. It was noted that due to a 
sharp reduction in tax revenues, a most complex situation had 
taken shape regarding the formation of the income part of the 
budget, which cast doubt on the government's ability in the near 
future to continue paying salaries to teachers, doctors, and 
other employees paid from the budget. 
  Akayev thanked members of the delegation for the work they 
had carried out, pointing out that he shared their concern and 
expressed his opinion about the issues discussed. 
  As a result of a dialogue that took place, a certain 
compromise was reached. It envisages a lower inflation rate, 
which Kyrgyzstan should achieve by reducing the budget deficit, 
a stricter credit and monetary policy, and a harsher financial 
discipline. If these conditions are met, the IMF will be ready 
to consider a program of further financial assistance on 
preferential terms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

