Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Karen Mishikyan: "Prophet in His Own Country"] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan -- T. Gdlyan, chairman of the Russian 
People's Party, who is in Armenia on family business, has given 
his prediction regarding the development of political events. 
He put forward two possible avenues: "Zhirinovskiy may quite 
possibly prefer a bloc with the Agrarians and the Communists in 
order to combat the democrats. But, once it has conquered the 
latter, the coalition would inevitably fall out among 
themselves." 
  Gdlyan believes that there are definite Western forces and 
mafia structures behind Zhirinovskiy. Touching on the subject 
of the LDPR [Liberal Democratic Party of Russia] leader's 
possibly coming to Armenia, he said that he has information that 
Zhirinovskiy receives financial backing from a number of 
influential Armenian businessmen in Armenia as well as in Russia. 

