<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, February 5 (SNARK) -- Three war planes 
of the Azerbaijani Air Force have again bombed this morning a 
number of populated areas in Nagorno-Karabakh. This time, the 
Mardakertskiy region settlements in the northern Karabakh were 
attacked. Victims among civilians were reported to SNARK by the 
Karabakh Defense Army press-service. Details are revealed. 
  Meanwhile, military activity continues already the third day 
on the eastern part of Martuninskiy region. This morning the 
Karabakh forces were able to reject the attack of Azerbaijani 
troops. After two-hour fight, the Azerbaijani side retreated to 
initial positions, bearing losses. 

