<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Names `Traitors'; Raps Serbia Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502194194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent A. Pishchayev; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] [Pishchayev] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's subtleties knew 
no bounds today. At a meeting with electors in Moscow, he 
warned that presidential elections will be held before the end 
of parliament's two-year term in office, that is, this year. 
  The LDPR [Liberal Democratic Party of Russia] together, of 
course, with its leader will come to power. 
  How can they not win if, as Vladimir Volfovich says, the 
government has betrayed the interests not only of the Russians 
but of all Slavs. Who do you think are the most inveterate 
traitors? 
  [Video shows Zhirinovskiy addressing meeting] [Begin 
Zhirinovskiy recording] These are the scoundrels in the current 
Russian Government: Kozyrev, Chubays, and Shokhin. [end 
recording] 
  [Pishchayev] At the same time, he was rude about Russia's 
Choice, calling the faction Russia's Rejects. Regarding the 
government in the Kremlin, he remarked that it is pandering to 
the West which is testing on Serbia a method to destroy Russia. 
Once it has destroyed the Serbs, Zhirinovskiy said, world 
imperialism -- familiar vocabulary this -- wants to settle 
Muslims on their land and encircle Russia with an Islamic cordon. 
  The LDPR leader also demanded that the United Nations cancel 
its sanctions against Serbia. He compared Mitterrand to Hitler, 
since the French president has proposed, in his words, bomb 
strikes against the Bosnian Serbs. 
  Also today, Zhirinovskiy advised the Russian president not 
to 
sign a friendship treaty with Georgia but offer it gubernare 
status within the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

