<H3> <TI>   Media Ban on Cabinet Meetings Revised </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402143994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1330 GMT 
4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has revised its decision to ban media 
access to sittings of the Russian Council of Ministers except 
for the ROSSIYASKAYA GAZETA newspaper. Valeriy Trishin, deputy 
head of the Cabinet's press service, has told INTERFAX that a 
decision has been adopted to allow representatives of state news 
agencies, television and radio companies, and ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA 
to attend sittings as observers. For other press bodies, 
Trishin said, briefings and news conferences by Cabinet members 
will be organized. 

