<H3> <TI>   Military Communications Satellite Launched </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502130594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0955 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS freelance correspondent Semen Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 5 Feb -- At 1146 Moscow time today, Russia's 
military space forces launched a Raduga-1 communications 
satellite from Baykonur cosmodrome, using a Proton heavy 
three-stage carrier rocket with a DM 2 [?dvigatel marshevyy, 
sustainer engine] unit. At the military space forces press 
center the ITAR-TASS correspondent learned that the launch was 
successful. The satellite is being guided by the main center for 
testing and guidance of spacecraft (Golitsino-2), which is a 
part of the military space force structure. 

</TEXT>

