<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parameters for Launch Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702090894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0849 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702090894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 7 TASS--A communications satellite, 
Raduga-1, was launched by a proton booster from the Baykonur 
cosmodrome on February 5, 1994. 
  The satellite carries multichannel relay equipment to boost 
telephone and telegraph radio communications over the territory 
of the Russian Federation. 
  The satellite was put into a near-stationary orbit with the 
following parameters: 
  distance from the Earth's surface -- 36,513 kilometers, 
  revolution period -- 24 hours 33 minutes, 
  orbital inclination -- 1.4 degrees. 
  Installed equipment operates smoothly. 
  The command and measurement complex exercises contol over 
the 
satellite. Work with the satellite will be conducted in 
compliance with a set programme. 

</TEXT>

