<F P=102>  LD0502144294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1420 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0502144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijan's army has been fiercely resisting an 
advancing Armenian force in northern Karabakh for the second day 
running. An Azerbaijani defence ministry spokesman reported to 
Interfax on Saturday that the enemy had been mounting attacks 
along the Kelbajar, Geranboi, and Terter lines. The Armenian 
losses in two days of fighting are estimated at 40 men, 2 tanks, 
and 1 armored vehicle. 
  On the southern front (down the Goradiz line), according to 
the spokesman, there have been sporadic battles. Azerbaijani 
army positions and villages were repeatedly shelled throughout 
Friday. Casualties are being specified. 

