<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Hands Over Files of KGB Pensioners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502112194 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2000 GMT 4 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Thursday [3 February] Lithuanian officials took 
over the files of KGB old-age pensioners residing in Lithuania. 
Earlier, the files, kept in the former KGB headquarters in 
Vilnius, were under the charge of a special KGB people group, 
subordinate to the Russian Embassy in Vilnius. The Baltic News 
Service reports that a conflict broke out while taking over the 
documents, as the women in charge of the dossiers refused to 
give them to Lithuanian officials. The authorized Russian 
official was not present during the handover of the documents, 
and the Russian Embassy in Vilnius refused to comment on the 
incident. The files of the KGB pensioners will now be kept in 
the Lithuanian archives and will be accessible to both 
Lithuanian and Russian officials. 

</TEXT>

