<H3> <TI>   Joint Maneuvers With U.S. in Far East Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402183794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1408 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow Feb 4 -- Russia and the United States will 
conduct joint military exercises in the Far East in July to 
train troops for operations conducted by peacekeeping forces. 
The exercises are expected to be held for a week on Russian 
territory, with the participation of a few units belonging to 
land troops, ITAR-TASS learned from a well-informed source in 
the Russian Defense Ministry today. 
  The possibility of conducting joint military exercises was 
discussed last year during a working meeting between Russian and 
U.S. defense Ministers in Bavaria in summer, and during the 
visit by the Russian defense minister to the United States in 
autumn. A final agreement on joint exercises was reached at the 
January U.S.- Russian summit in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

