<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs Ruling on Russian-U.S. Enterprise Fund </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402112994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0705 GMT 
4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia's president has signed a ruling on measures 
to assist the activity of the Russian-American Enterprise Fund. 
The Russian State Property Management Committee has been 
charged with coordinating work to assist the fund's activity. 
The committee may call on the Finance Ministry for help. 
  Robert Talbin, the fund's general director, has said the 
fund's activity will cover economically advantageous Russian 
enterprises with up to 2,500 staff, with production of consumer 
goods being the object of its attention. As initial capital, 
the fund will receive 340 million dollars from the U.S. 
Government. In the future, the fund intends to attract 
contributions by organizations and private persons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

