<H3> <TI>   DPRK Envoy Denies Russia Joining in DPRK Nuclear Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0702121894 Moscow Radio Moscow in Korean 1000 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0702121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with a ITAR-TASS reporter on Friday 
[4 February], the DPRK Ambassador to Russia Son Song-pil pointed 
out that the allegation that Russian nuclear physics scholars 
participated in Pyongyang's nuclear arms development is 
groundless and false. 
  Stressing that the DPRK has never implemented any military 
nuclear program, he said that the DPRK has limited research 
projects to totally peace-oriented nuclear energy development. 
  The DPRK ambassador pointed out that Japanese press 
organizations have spread such a false rumor. 

