<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Receives Vietnamese Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702085294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0823 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 7 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev, who is due to fly to Uzbekistan later today, met 
Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam on Monday morning [7 
February] for talks on bilateral Russian-Vietnamese relations 
and the situation in the Asian-Pacific region. 
  The Vietnamese minister, who arrived in Moscow on his way 
back home from a visit to the commonwealth Central Asian 
republics, told Kozyrev about his impressions from the visit and 
confirmed his invitation to the Russian minister to visit 
Vietnam. 
  "We are progressing fairly well in our relations," Kozyrev 
said before the talks. "We meet three-four times a year, and 
working meetings also take place on other levels. In 
particular, the development of economic cooperation between 
Russia and Vietnam are being discussed on a wide scale". 
  Minister Kozyrev called for speeding up joint work on 
drafting a bilateral treaty between Vietnam and Russia. 

</TEXT>

