<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 7 TASS -- "Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev met Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam 
to discuss preparations for the visit to Russia by the 
Vietnamese prime minister scheduled approximately at the end of 
June," Galina Sidorova, a political adviser of the Russian 
foreign minister, told ITAR-TASS upon completion of the meeting. 
  Sidorova said that Russo-Vietnamese commission for trade, 
technical and economic cooperation would meet in session in 
April, 1994 as part of the preparations for the visit. The 
commission will discuss a number of other economic agreements, 
Sidorova said. 
  She pointed out that Russia's goal is to sign a political 
document on basic principles of relations between Russia and 
Vietnam during the visit. 
  During the talks the Vietnamese foreign minister shared his 
impressions of the visit to Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan. For his 
part, the Russian minister told about his recent official visit 
to China. The sides exchanged opinions on the current situation 
in the Asian pacific region and problems of cooperation on 
security in the framework of ASEAN. Special attention at the 
talks was devoted to the present situation in Bosnia. 

