<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Expresses `Anger' at Sarajevo Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602121194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1149 
GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 6 Feb--"We are outraged [my vozmushcheny] at 
the act of terrorism in Sarajevo that led to the deaths of many 
citizens of this city, which has suffered so much," says a 
statement of the Russian Federation Foreign Ministry issued 
today. The document stresses the need "to carry out a swift and 
objective investigation and to inform the world public about its 
findings". "Those guilty of this atrocity, whoever they are, 
must be severely punished", the Russian Foreign Ministry 
statement stresses. 
  As already reported, about 60 people were killed and over 
200 
injured on Saturday when a mortar shell exploded. 

</TEXT>

