<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Christopher Discuss Yugoslavia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702121094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Last night, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
held a telephone conversation with the U.S. secretary of state 
during which the two men discussed the problem of a Bosnian 
settlement. Galina Sidorova, adviser to the Russian foreign 
minister, said that air strikes against any of the warring sides 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina would be justified if they prompted these 
sides to accept a compromise. However, she feels that in 
present circumstances, such strikes would only lead to a further 
brutalization of the conflict. 

