<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev, France's Leotard Sign Cooperation Agreements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402115594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1122 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 4 TASS -- Two Russo-French 
intergovernmental agreements -- on defence cooperation and on 
military-techical cooperation -- were signed in the Russian 
Defence Ministry on Friday. This is the chief result of talks 
between General of the Army Pavel Grachev, Russian minister of 
defence, and his French counterpart, Francois Leotard, who is 
currently in Russia on an official visit. 
  The defence cooperation agreement provides for exchanges of 
military delegations and consultations on defence matters. The 
military-technical cooperation accord envisages joint tackling 
of defence industry conversion matters, the development of some 
types of armaments and military hardware, those for the Air 
Force, in particular, and the coordination of matters concerning 
arms trade with third countries. 
  The agreements signed bring Russia and France to a 
qualitatively new level of relations, the two ministers 
emphasised during their meeting. 
  M. Leotard together with Grachev visited the Taman Guards 
Motorised Rifle Division, took in specimens of arms and combat 
hardware, and familiarised himself with the living conditions of 
personnel. 
  The French guest's trip to the Tula Airborne Division, 
scheduled for Friday, has been cancelled. 

</TEXT>

