<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Leotard Discuss Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502102294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0502102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 5 TASS -- Both Moscow and Paris 
favour a further development of Russian-French cooperation, 
specifically, in the military-technical and conversion spheres, 
Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev and French Defence 
Minister Francois Leotard, now on a visit here, announced today 
at their meeting in the Russian Foreign Ministry. 
  Welcoming the French defence minister, Kozyrev pointed out 
that Russia and France, the military and the diplomats of the 
two countries, had traditionally maintained close ties. The 
Russian Foreign Ministry is maintaining the same relations with 
the Russian Defence Ministry and Minister Pavel Grachev. "We 
even agreed with our minister to create `allied 
military-diplomatic troops'," Kozyrev joked. This does not 
mean, however, that Russian imperialism is being revived, he 
continued and urged not to believe such allegations. "What is 
being revived is the normal statehood of Russia," Kozyrev 
stressed. 
  "Our talks in Moscow are an integral part of the overall 
efforts, aimed at the development of bilateral relations and 
cooperation and the revival of the Russian-French alliance in a 
new setting," he said. 
  The ministers discussed problems dealing with the 
strengthening of stability on the European continent, the 
Bosnian settlement and the staging of peace-keeping operations, 
including on the territory of the former USSR. The conversation 
was held in an atmosphere, which reflected the relations of 
partnership taking shape between Russia and France. 

</TEXT>

