<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Against Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402203894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1752 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Russian Liberal 
Democratic Party, said his party's group in the State Duma would 
unanimously vote against the ratification of the 
Russian-Georgian Treaty on Friendship, Good-Neighborly Relations 
and Cooperation signed in Tbilisi on Thursday [3 February]. 
  "Two hundred years ago Georgia became part of Russia forever 
as Tiflis [Tbilisi] Province and had no right to secede. For us 
Georgia is a state that does not exist," Zhirinovskiy told 
Interfax. 
  He said Georgia should be allowed to exist on its own, 
"without Russian subsidies, without our assistance." "Let 
Turkish troops come and show them what Turkish democracy means 
if they don't want Russian democracy," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-36503 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov025_a_94029" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-025 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

