<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Concerned Over Russian Troop Presence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0402222294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1316 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0402222294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, February 4 (SNARK)--At the meeting with the 
leadership of the Russian Defence Department the representatives 
of the Georgian delegation put a question on additional 
redistribution to Georgia the additional content of Russian 
troops within the intermediary mission, Colonel Pavel Flyagin 
[name as received], the expert of the Transcaucasia Ethnic 
Relations of the Russian Defence Department, told SNARK. 
  According to Flyagin, Armenia also is interested in the 
Russian troops presence on her territory. Mr. Flyagin said the 
Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan discussed the problem at 
the recent negotiations with the Heads of the Group of the 
Russian Troops in Transcaucasia. 
  Speaking on the results of the negotiations which took place 
between military Heads of Russian and Georgia, Pavel Flyagin 
informed of the meeting's agenda - the sides discussed on the 
legal and other kinds of guarantees for the Russian soldiers as 
the latter are waiting for the solution of their social, life 
and other problems. Mr. Flyagin hopes the sides will do their 
best to solve the problems in the coming future. 

</TEXT>

