<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Cooperation Planned With Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502104194 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0900 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Recently, the Georgian minister of agriculture and 
food production and the Turkish minister of agriculture and 
rural affairs signed a protocol on technical, scientific, and 
economic cooperation between the two ministries in Ankara. It 
contains four paragraphs and stipulates the extension of 
cooperation in the spheres of agriculture, food production, 
cattle-breeding, and fisheries. Our correspondent Dilar 
Jvebenava has been told at the ministry that Turkish experts are 
expected to visit in the very near future and will carry out 
research of conditions for cooperation. This will be followed 
by a return visit by our delegation. Thus, partnership with a 
neighbor is useful, especially with Turkey as a wealthy, 
politically stable, and economically strong country, which is in 
line with European standards and where the Georgian diaspora is 
best represented. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

