<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Servicemen Attempt To Seize Black Sea Fleet Unit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502121594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1137 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 5 Feb -- More than 300 Ukrainian servicemen 
attempted on Friday to seize the territory of a military unit of 
the Black Sea Fleet in Nikolayev (southern Ukraine). Around 10 
of them were armed with automatic weapons, an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent was informed by phone today by the fleet's press 
center. Only restraint on the part of the command of the 
brigade of ships under construction and of a hospital, which the 
attackers penetrated, prevented a more serious incident from 
occurring. 
  It says the Ukrainian side regarded as justification for 
these actions the fact that three officers and five warrant 
officers of the hospital base submitted applications with a 
request to serve in the Ukrainian Navy. At the same time, these 
Black Sea servicemen intend to move under the jurisdiction of 
the Ukrainian Defense Ministry together with material resources, 
equipment, and weapons. 
  "The position of the Black Sea Command remains invariable: 
we 
are not going to impede those who want to serve in the Ukrainian 
Navy," an ITAR-TASS correspondent was told at the fleet's press 
center. 
  However, all units, bases, ships and other military 
installations belonging to the fleet remain under the 
jurisdiction of the Black Sea Fleet command, as follows from the 
Yalta agreement signed by the presidents of Russia and Ukraine. 
Only the signatures of the two presidents can authorize any 
actions with regard to the fleet. 
  The press center voiced its regret that the unwillingness to 
understand this undermined the authority of the representatives 
of the command of the Ukrainian Navy who have been lately 
talking with increasing frequency about their desire to conduct 
a dialogue with the fleet's command. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

