<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Makes Counterintelligence Appointments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402203594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1752 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin appointed by decree 
on Friday General-Lieutenants Andrey Bykov, Aleksandr Strelkov 
and Valeriy Timofeyev as deputies director of the Russian 
Counter-Intelligence Service, the presidential press service 
reports. 
  Lieutenant-Colonel Aleksandr Mikhailov was appointed as the 
Chief of the Public Relations Center. 

</TEXT>

